cmdjy89y0037ysbrcsafik5b4	Medicine And Literature Without Borders (E-Book)	One of the key strengths of this book is its interdisciplinary approach, which draws on\r\\ninsights from literature, medicine, history, sociology, and psychology. The contributors to\r\\nthis volume offer a range of perspectives, from the clinical and scientific to the cultural and\r\\nhumanistic. This diversity of perspectives ensures that the book comprehensively explores\r\\nthe intersection of literature and medicine in Nigeria. The diversity includes how literature\r\\ncan inform medical practice, including narrative medicine, medical humanities, and\r\\nliterary medicine; how medicine familiarizes the readers with medical imageries and\r\\nsymbolism in literary works; and how society perceives health and illness, especially in the\r\\nNigerian context. This book, Medicine and Literature Without Borders: Health and\r\\nSocial Justice in the Writings of Wale Okediran,is rich with sights, offering pathways to\r\\nnew research and disciplinary opportunities. It honors the genius represented in the life and\r\\nwork of Dr. Okediran. It is the best in Nigerian Studies to cumulate Dr. Okediran's career\r\\nand reflections in multiple ways. As the book highlights the contributions of Dr. Okediran,\r\\nit also leads us to the positive arena of ideas and research.	2000	100	[{"public_id": null, "secure_url": "http://accessiblepublishers.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/Okediran-Book-front-Cover-scaled.jpg"}]	cmdjwh6rm0000sb2qdvkmpwaf	\N	e_book	t	active	\N	\N	\N	WALE OKEDIRAN	\N	\N	2025-07-26 07:48:50.904	2025-08-04 08:20:23.444	t	17011	E8559092	\N	\N	f	f	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	2613
