cmdjy897m035isbrcze6q5prh	Once Upon An Elephant (E-Book)	<strong>About the book </strong>\r\\n\r\\nEvery human society has its own procedure of governance, a balanced relationship/ contract between the rulers and the ruled; it is a mechanism which ensures that social cohesion is forged and translated into progressive development. If, and when this procedure and/or mechanism is trampled upon or put in disrepute by greed and treachery, the tragic reality can best be imagined. Indeed, it is this dislocation that ONCE UPON AN ELEPHANT dramatizes. The play chimes as an engaging piece of theatre, historical reality and socio-political metaphor, which touches on the Nigerian life and with palpable vividness as a commentary on the seeming unending leadership/followership crisis of the African Continent.\r\\n\r\\n<strong>About the Author</strong>\r\\n\r\\nBosede Funke Ademilua-Afolayan is an Associate Professor in the Department of English, University of Lagos. She is the author of Look Back in Gratitude and Once Upon an Elephant, first published by Kraftbooks, lbadan. Her first collection of poems is entitled "Conversations" published by Malthouse, Lagos in 2022. She edited a collection of essays entitled Nigerian Female Dramatists: Expression, Resistance, Agency, in 2021, published by Routledge. Ademilua-Afolayan is also a Commonwealth Fellow. Her areas of specialisation include comparative drama, African literature, women's studies, creative writing and Nollywood studies. She can be reached at afolayanbosede@gmail.com.	500	100	[{"public_id": null, "secure_url": "http://accessiblepublishers.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/once-upon-an-elephant-cover.jpg"}]	cmdjwh6rm0000sb2qdvkmpwaf	\N	e_book	t	active	\N	\N	\N	<strong>About the book </strong>\r\\n\r\\nEvery human society has its own procedure of governance, a balanced relationship/ contract between the rulers and the ruled; it is a mechanism which ensures that social cohesion is forged and translated into progressive development. If, and when this procedure and/or mechanism is trampled upon or put in disrepute by greed and treachery, the tragic reality can best be imagined. Indeed, it is this dislocation that ONCE UPON AN ELEPHANT dramatizes. The play chimes as an engaging piece of theatre, historical reality and socio-political metaphor, which touches on the Nigerian life and with palpable vividness as a commentary on the seeming unending leadership/followership crisis of the African Continent.	\N	\N	2025-07-26 07:48:49.954	2025-07-26 07:48:49.954	f	15880	ELE0000I	\N	\N	f	f	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	639
cmdjy86b102uusbrcnkv3vhdm	The Benue (E-Book)	About the Book\r\\n\r\\nA saga of mixed feelings.\r\\n\r\\nA melodrama of inexplicable uncertainty, discordant to the nothingness reasoner. To say love is a crime is like to infer that it is a sin to love. But the inimical appreciates the pulchritude connected to the concluding part of the novel. The life of a young American girl who is a musician would be turned upside down due to marrying a charming young Nigerian man and deciding to come to Nigeria for the holiday with her husband.\r\\n\r\\nThey say culture is a way of life, of a particular people.\r\\n\r\\nThe tragedy that leads to her husband's death also makes her go through the clutches of widowhood in "The Benue."\r\\n\r\\nDisclaimer: This book is a fiction and is subjected to the author's thought process.	800	100	[{"public_id": null, "secure_url": "http://accessiblepublishers.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/THE-BENUE-COVER.jpg"}]	cmdjwh6rm0000sb2qdvkmpwaf	\N	e_book	t	active	\N	\N	\N	WINSALA 'GBOTEMI	\N	\N	2025-07-26 07:48:46.189	2025-07-26 07:48:46.189	f	15078	EL00002520	\N	\N	f	f	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	1009
