cmdjy8255027msbrcsq2w4iof	Walls and Bridges (E-Book)	About the Book\r\\n\r\\nHIV/AIDS is a pandemic that has caused grief in homes, schools and our society at large. Walls and Bridges is a touching dramatic story of "Oyin”, whose parents died from HIVIAIDS. Because of Oyin's predicament she was rejected at school, by friends and family thinking that she had also been infected.\r\\n\r\\nThe story teaches us how we should rightly treat people who have one way or the other become a victim of the cold hands of HIV/AIDS with love, care and affection and not stigmatize them.	450	100	[{"public_id": null, "secure_url": "http://accessiblepublishers.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/EL000066-1.jpg"}]	cmdjwh6rm0000sb2qdvkmpwaf	\N	e_book	t	active	\N	\N	\N	Niyi Josef	\N	\N	2025-07-26 07:48:40.793	2025-07-26 07:48:40.793	f	12159	EL000066	\N	\N	f	f	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	522
cmdjy86td02wqsbrcciqjzids	Ras Basic Cret and Cult Bk 3 (E-Book)	BASIC CREATIVE &amp; CULTURAL ARTS\r\\n\r\\nBasic Creative and Cultural Arts 1-6 is aptly designed in the basic form as the name implies by an expert in childhood education on the basis of the Nigerian primary schools creative art syllabus.\r\\n\r\\nThe book is carefully put together to create awareness in the subject and assist the children in bringing out various creative abilities that are latent in them.\r\\n\r\\nThe title contains interesting activities and exercises that encourage full participation of the children.\r\\n\r\\nThis book will go a long way in solving the problems of teaching and learning of the subject in our schools.\r\\n\r\\nThe author was born in the city of Ibadan, Nigeria in the 60s. He attended primary school between 1970-1975 in Ogbomoso and Igbo-Elerin Grammar School Ibadan for his secondary school education between\r\\n\r\\n1977-1982. He proceeded to The Polytechnic Ibadan, Eruwa campus for OND in Fine Arts between 1986-1988.\r\\n\r\\nHe furthered to Yaba College of Technology Lagos\r\\n\r\\nfor his HND, specializing in Painting from 1992-1995.\r\\n\r\\nIn his quest for more knowledge, he went to the University of Ibadan for PDGE in the year 2001, then to the Ekiti State University where he obtained B.A ED in Fine and Applied Arts specializing in painting between 2004-2007.\r\\n\r\\nKolade is a prolific book illustrator, an author, a painter of repute, a teacher, art-historian and cultural artist. He holds a Masters degree in Visual Arts from the Institute of African Studies University of Ibadan, Nigeria.	735	100	[{"public_id": null, "secure_url": "http://accessiblepublishers.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/CCA-3-front-scaled.jpg"}]	cmdjwh6rm0000sb2qdvkmpwaf	\N	e_book	t	active	\N	\N	\N	Kolade Salami,Eddy Krajcar,Aikipitanyi	\N	\N	2025-07-26 07:48:46.849	2025-07-26 07:48:46.849	f	15203	EP000006	\N	\N	f	f	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	1009
