cmdjy822b0272sbrc8i74qhm9	New Wave English Pry 5 (E-Book)	New waves\r\\n\r\\nENGLISH\r\\n\r\\nFor Primary Schools\r\\n\r\\nNew Waves English for Primary Schools is written by a team of experienced classroom teachers. It follows a thematic arrangement and approach dictated by the 9-year Basic Education Programme.\r\\n\r\\nIt has a teacher-pupil friendly approach which facilitates easy learning and assimilation of the topics treated.\r\\n\r\\nThe book is sub-divided into:\r\\n\r\\nSpeech Sounds - This teaches the pupils about phonics. The pupils are taught how to pronounce words in their original sounds based on the sounds that each letter represents.\r\\n\r\\nListening and Speaking - Where pupils are asked questions based on dialogue.\r\\n\r\\nGrammar - Where pupils develop skills in answering comprehension questions.\r\\n\r\\nReading - Where pupils develop skills in answering comprehension questions\r\\n\r\\nVocabulary exercise - Pupils learn the meanings of new words by checking them up in the dictionary.\r\\n\r\\nWriting composition - Helps pupils to improve their writing skills.\r\\n\r\\nThe book generally promotes language learning through activity-based exercises, enables pupils to acquire English Language skills in an easy manner and makes the language for an enjoyable reading. It is a good companion not only to the pupils and teachers but also to the parents and guardians.	1190	100	[{"public_id": null, "secure_url": "http://accessiblepublishers.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/EP000279-scaled.jpg"}]	cmdjwh6rm0000sb2qdvkmpwaf	\N	e_book	t	active	\N	\N	\N	'BIOLA OPATAYO	\N	\N	2025-07-26 07:48:40.691	2025-07-26 07:48:40.691	f	12149	EP000279	\N	\N	f	f	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	1442
